This post is to Bob Rogers. If you want to see the burnouts they are there to be seen. It is more difficult to see the one's who came back and struggled to make a successful life. I have been married to the same woman for 26 years and worked at the same job for 26 years. These are the focus and the anchors that enabled me to get through. The vets are still out there. I am 50 now and it is time to do a lot of reflection. This forum gives me the opportunity to post and talk to other vets. And share info with people who ask NOW what was it like. When I came back they didn't want to know or didn't care.<br>
The other thing that was brought out to me the other day was:<br>
The Viet Nam Conflict is a far removed from todays young people as WW II was for me.<br>
Boy, it's scary when you think about it in that form. But then we all know it's a bitch to get old.
